Product Description

High Quality Kids Pedometer Watch

NO need to contect smartphone or download a APP. This step tracker watch is perfectly tailored for kids, blending fun with functionality. It encourages active lifestyles while keeping track of every step they take, fostering a love for movement and health from an early age.

Multifunction Watch

Date/Time; Steps counting, Distance traveled, Calories burned ; Waterproof, Shock Resistant; Stopwatch, Daily Alarm Clock, 12H/24H format is changeable;

IP67 Waterproof

Feel free to wear the watch for showering, washing hands, playing with water.(Note: It is not supported for use in hot water, and can't wear it in a hot bath or sauna)

Vibrating Alarm Clock

Support to set 2 alarm clock at the same time on your watch; Vibration alarm clock , just wake wearer up, will not disturbing others.

Easy to Charge

Built-in USB charging head, you can charge the watch with any USB adapter (Such as phone adapter, power bank, computer).

Comfortable to Wear

Food-grade silicone strap plus spray handfeel oil will more comfortable and more soft fit your wrist. Easy to detach watch strap and change different color style strap.

Kids Fitness Parter

Except viewing the time, you can also view your daily steps. The watch will accurately track your steps.

Great Gift for Teens and Kids

With bright and bright colors, compact design, and a variety of practical functions, it will be a very suitable watch for students, teenagers, and Children.

    How customer reviews and ratings work

    Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

    To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we dont use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

    4 out of 5 stars
    Rechargeable Time Piece
    I've never owned a rechargeable watch before (like an actual watch, not a smart watch) so I didn't know what to expect. It's not bad... my one complaint is the time doesn't stay on, so you need to press the button to show it. That's a bit odd because since I was a child digital watched were a thing, and those always stayed on and lasted for quite some time. So, this watch doesn't beat those el cheapo $1 cereal box watches in that regard.It has date and year functionality as well (same as the other digital watches), and a step counter and a few more screens I won't be using. It feels great, comfortable to wear on your hand, and can be charged by removing the portion seen in my picture and inserting it directly.Not a bad watch, but it doesn't do anything extraordinary.

    • Closer Look
      3.0 out of 5 stars Step Counting Feature Is Unreliable. Attractive, Simple Design. Charges Easily.
      Reviewed in the United States on January 21, 2025
      Color: Deep BlueAmazon Vine Customer Review of Free Product( What's this? )
      I ordered this watch for myself, not for a child; it was inexpensive and simple in design. I did not want a watch that synced to my phone. I am an older adult who simply wanted to know how many steps I was taking each day.
      The navy band and shape of this watch appeal to me. The ease of charging it by removing it from the band and plugging it into a USB socket is a bonus. It holds a charge for days. I like that I can use it instead of a phone to tell the time, so I dont feel obliged to carry a phone. The time is shown in large numberseasy to read. Like others, I dont like having to press a button to determine the time, but then again, I dont want large digital numerals lighting up my wrist all day long, either.
      The most concerning issue I have with the watch is that it doesnt accurately record the number of steps I take. Sometimes it is way off. Today, for example, when I had walked at least a mile, I checked the watch and found that it had recorded only 316 steps.
      So, now I have a multi-functional watch that I rely upon only for time. I might end up with a pedometer. Though I like its looks, is not the watch I had hoped it would be.

    • Cid Herman
      5.0 out of 5 stars Does the basics very well and looks good on my wrist.
      Reviewed in the United States on January 14, 2025
      Color: BlackAmazon Vine Customer Review of Free Product( What's this? )
      My first impression of the FOCWONY DIGITAL WATERPROOF PEDOMETER WATCH was that it would be a big hassle to charge. But I have since revised that opinion, chalking it up to the learning curve of a new way of doing things. This watch charges via USB, but it needs no cable. What it does have is a USB plug that sticks out of it that goes directly into any USB charger or directly into a USB charging port. In order to charge it, you need to remove the watch from the watchband. It is a little bit of a hassle, but it doesn't need to be charged very often, and it sits nicely in any power strip or outlet that has a USB port. That eliminates the need for both the charger and the cable. That convenience makes up for having to take it out of the band for charging. It took me a minute to get it oriented correctly to fit it in the USB outlet, but it sits in there quite solid.

      I like this watch. I think it's attractive. I think it works perfectly for all the functions that it does, which are mostly basic. It keeps track of steps. It has an alarm, it has a light, and it has a calendar. It has nice, large numbers in the display so you don't have to move your face closer to read them. It is easy to reset the steps when you start a new run or a new day. That's basically the extent of what I want anyway. I don't want something that has to connect to the Internet or that answers my phone for me. That's too invasive, in my opinion.

      From what I can tell, it's extremely accurate at tracking steps and keeping time. It adds steps to the count after you take 17 in a row to prevent false positives. And it looks really good. It's also very inexpensive. That combination is enough for me to give it five stars. It's a winner in my book.

      Rechargeable Time Piece

      Reviewed in the United States on January 3, 2025
      I've never owned a rechargeable watch before (like an actual watch, not a smart watch) so I didn't know what to expect. It's not bad... my one complaint is the time doesn't stay on, so you need to press the button to show it. That's a bit odd because since I was a child digital watched were a thing, and those always stayed on and lasted for quite some time. So, this watch doesn't beat those el cheapo $1 cereal box watches in that regard.

      It has date and year functionality as well (same as the other digital watches), and a step counter and a few more screens I won't be using. It feels great, comfortable to wear on your hand, and can be charged by removing the portion seen in my picture and inserting it directly.

      Not a bad watch, but it doesn't do anything extraordinary.
